article.description: Julie Wojta scored 24 points, Kayla Tetschlag had 21 and Wisconsin-Green Bay (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today, No. 22 AP) stayed unbeaten with a 78-60 win over Cleveland State on Saturday in a rematch of last season's Horizon League championship game.
article.headline: Wis.-Green Bay stays undefeated in Horizon League title game rematch
article.linkText: Wojta, Wis.-Green Bay crush Cleveland State
article.story:
CLEVELAND -- Julie Wojta scored 24 points, Kayla Tetschlag had 21 and Wisconsin-Green Bay (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today, No. 22 AP) stayed unbeaten with a 78-60 win over Cleveland State on Saturday.

Wojta added seven rebounds and seven assists while shooting 9 of 10. Celeste Hoewisch added 12 points and six assists for Wisconsin-Green Bay.

Shawnita Garland had 22 points for the Vikings (5-7, 0-1), who committed 24 turnovers. Cleveland State pulled to within 47-43 with 13:25 remaining, but went more than four minutes without a field goal as the Phoenix (12-0, 1-0) slowly pulled away.

Jessica Roque had 12 points for Cleveland State and Kailey Klein added 11.

The Phoenix are 46-4 overall against Cleveland State.
